The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Saturday, November 01, 2003  30-day city season from Nov. 5 
 BY STAR RACER				 										Calcutta: The stake-money of Rs 3 crore will be up for grabs during the 30-day city winter season starting November 5. The prize-money has been hiked by nearly 25 percent and the number of race days has also been increased compa-red to last winter, informed S. K. Bose, the government nominated RCTC,steward at the pre-season media-conference on Friday. The horse-strength has also improved significantly to 366, and more horses from D. Byramjis and MAM Ramas-wamys yards are expected during the season. RCTC will again hold Breeze up sales on November 17, and from Saturday, a revised grand prize scheme  against totalisator tickets holders for both, the inter-venue and the live racing , will come into operation. The free entry coupons scheme stands withdrawn.
